  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b90\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Warning issued by the United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs on Sri Lanka",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA) says the current economic crisis in Sri Lanka is likely to turn into a full-fledged emergency humanitarian crisis.",
        "The United Nations has indicated that there is a shortage of about 200 types of essential medicines in Sri Lanka and another 163 types of essential medicines will be in short supply in the next two or three months.",
        "In addition, the United Nations has indicated that there is a shortage of more than 2,700 medical equipment needed for surgery and more than 250 general laboratory equipment, and that many hospitals have had to postpone emergency surgeries due to continuous power outages and shortages of fuel needed to run generators.",
        "Against this backdrop, the United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs has warned that the entire economic crisis could turn into a humanitarian emergency."
      ],
